The paper discusses the use of computational models to simulate human selective attention, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential applications of these models in robotics, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
